<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="777" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.52/132: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-23T17:00:00+00:00">October 23, 1936—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>X–239. In view of serious situation and present indications Embassy
                                will again be opened as place of refuge. Military Attaché has been
                                placed in charge of important matters in connection therewith, for
                                which he is qualified. Please inform War.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>